-- Pernod-Ricard First-Quarter Sales Climb 10%, Exceeding Analyst Estimates
-- B y   C l e m e n t i n e   F l e t c h e r
-- 2010-10-21T05:30:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/pernod-ricard-first-quarter-sales-climb-10-exceeding-analyst-estimates.html
Pernod-Ricard SA, the maker of
Chivas Regal whiskey and Absolut vodka, said first-quarter
“organic” sales, which exclude the effect of acquisitions,
disposals or currency swings, soared 10 percent, beating a 4.5
percent median growth estimate of 8 analysts surveyed by
Bloomberg News.  The Paris-based company said that so-called organic profit
growth from recurring operations will be “close to 6 percent”
this year, compared with 4 percent last year. The company has
previously issued guidance for the year at its annual general
meeting, which is scheduled for Nov. 10 this year.The company
commented today in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Clementine Fletcher at 
 cfletcher5@bloomberg.net  